      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Burgundy, France</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">A practical Burgundy starting point with red fruit, earth, and enough shape to show what Pinot Noir from Burgundy does differently from Bordeaux blends.</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Variety:</strong> Pinot Noir</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-gray-100">
